VPN Gateway; Employee email
2 — Reconnaissance
BloodHound and SharpHound enumerate Active Directory to identify the shortest privilege escalation path to domain admin, while RustScan sweeps internal ranges to inventory file servers, application servers, and backup infrastructure — building the target map used to maximize encryption coverage in the final phase.[5,7]
BloodHound / SharpHound; RustScan
Active Directory; Internal network topology
3 — Persistence & Credential Harvest
A custom PowerShell script (IPScanner.ps1) is pushed silently to all domain-joined endpoints via GPO, running on every user logon and extracting saved passwords from Chrome's SQLite credential store. Collected databases are staged to SYSVOL — giving operators plaintext credentials to financial portals, email, and VPNs across the entire domain during a silent 72-hour window before encryption fires.[6]
IPScanner.ps1 (custom GPO-deployed script); Chrome SQLite (Login Data); SYSVOL staging
Group Policy / SYSVOL; Chrome browser (enterprise deployment)
4 — Lateral Movement
With domain admin credentials obtained from the BloodHound escalation path or Chrome harvest, affiliates pivot freely via RDP, WMI, and PsExec — no additional tooling required once domain admin is held. Mimikatz dumps LSASS on high-value hosts to harvest further credentials for any remaining restricted systems.[5,7]
PsExec; WMI; Mimikatz (LSASS dump); RDP
Windows domain-joined servers; LSASS process
5 — Exfiltration
Loan records, insurance policy data, and customer PII are transferred to attacker-controlled cloud storage via Cyberduck or rclone hours before encryption triggers — establishing the double-extortion position. If the ransom is refused, publication on Qilin's dark web DLS independently triggers LGPD breach notification obligations regardless of payment.[5,6]
Cyberduck (S3-compatible transfer); rclone
File servers; Loan & policy databases; Customer PII stores
6 — Encryption & Impact
A GPO-scheduled task fires simultaneously across every domain-joined Windows system — there is no sequential spread and no containment window once execution begins. bcdedit forces a safe mode reboot beforehand to strip endpoint protection, shadow copies are deleted to eliminate local recovery, and Windows event logs are wiped post-execution to frustrate forensic response.[5,6,7]
Qilin.B (Rust payload); GPO scheduled task; bcdedit; vssadmin; wmic shadowcopy
All domain-joined Windows endpoints and servers; Backup infrastructure; VSS snapshots


