3 — MFA Bypass
Where helpdesk manipulation alone is insufficient, SIM swapping gives operators direct control of the victim's phone number to intercept SMS OTPs, while push bombing bombards the victim with repeated Okta or Microsoft Authenticator approval requests until fatigue leads to acceptance — both techniques operate entirely independently of the victim's password.[11]
SIM swap (carrier social engineering); MFA fatigue / push bombing; Okta admin console
Employee mobile number; Okta MFA; Microsoft Authenticator
4 — Identity Platform Compromise
Okta admin access is used immediately to create backdoor admin accounts that survive any subsequent password reset, while Microsoft Graph API enumerates all Azure AD users, groups, roles, and conditional access policies. BYOVD drivers disable EDR on compromised endpoints, and infostealers vacuum browser session cookies and VPN credentials for further lateral movement.[11]
Okta admin API; Microsoft Graph API; WarZone RAT; Raccoon / Vidar Stealer; BYOVD drivers
Okta tenant; Azure AD / Entra ID; Endpoint EDR (disabled via BYOVD); Browser session cookies
5 — Microsoft 365 Data Exfiltration
Stolen Graph API tokens — which survive password resets — provide read access to every M365 resource the compromised account can reach, enabling bulk download of SharePoint loan documentation, OneDrive policy files, and Exchange mailboxes without any additional authentication. The activity is logged but indistinguishable from legitimate sync traffic without behavioral baselining.[11,12]
Microsoft Graph API; SharePoint REST API; Exchange Web Services; attacker-controlled cloud storage
SharePoint (loan documentation, policy files); OneDrive (employee files); Exchange (internal communications)
6 — Extortion / Escalation
Operators contact the organization directly via Telegram, citing LGPD liability and threatening to publish loan records, policy data, and internal communications on the ShinySp1d3r DLS — using regulatory fines of up to 2% of annual revenue as explicit pressure. If extortion fails, ransomware is deployed through SLH's 90% revenue-share agreement with RansomHub, converting the data theft into a full encryption incident.[10,11]
Telegram; ShinySp1d3r DLS; RansomHub payload (90% revenue share)
