1 — Initial Access
OPERA1ER invests in OSINT to identify exactly the right recipient before sending — macro-enabled Office documents arrive in finance staff inboxes disguised as payment confirmations, regulatory filings, or financial statements tailored to the target organization. Opening the document triggers a VBA macro that executes the initial payload silently in the background.[1,14]
