Finance staff email; Microsoft Office (Excel/Word); Employee workstations in accounts payable and treasury
2 — RAT Deployment & Persistence
The macro drops Netwire RAT or a Metasploit agent, establishing a full-featured remote access foothold with keylogging, screen capture, file transfer, and shell capabilities. Multiple redundant persistence mechanisms — scheduled tasks and registry run keys — are set simultaneously so that removing one does not evict the operator.[1]
Netwire RAT; Metasploit Framework agents; VBA macro dropper; Windows Scheduled Tasks; Registry run keys
Windows Task Scheduler; Windows Registry; Employee workstations; Corporate network
3 — Internal Reconnaissance
OPERA1ER's signature is patience — operators spend 3 to 12 months silently mapping the environment via Netwire keylogging, screen capture, and living-off-the-land discovery tools. They observe real payment workflows over weeks to learn approval thresholds, authorization chains, and transaction timing before touching a single financial system.[1,14]
Netwire RAT (keylogging, screen capture); Living-off-the-land binaries (net.exe, ipconfig, whoami, nltest); password dumping tools
Active Directory; Internal network topology; Payment system interfaces; Finance team workstations; Credential stores
4 — Lateral Movement
Movement toward payment terminals and treasury workstations is deliberate and unhurried — operators use legitimate admin tools and harvested credentials to avoid triggering anomaly-based detection. The target is always the person with payment authorization privileges, not the infrastructure itself.[1]
RDP; PsExec; WMI; Pass-the-Hash; harvested domain credentials
Finance department workstations; Payment processing terminals; Treasury management systems; Domain controller
5 — Payment System Access & Fraud Execution
Using credentials harvested during the reconnaissance phase, operators access loan disbursement, interbank transfer, or insurance claims payment systems and inject fraudulent transactions or modify legitimate ones to redirect funds. Transactions are timed to local banking hours and sized to stay below detection thresholds, with multiple simultaneous transfers dispersed across money mule accounts to compress the response window.[1,14]
Legitimate payment platform credentials (harvested); Remote desktop access; Transaction modification or injection
Loan disbursement platform; Insurance claims payment system; Interbank transfer interface
6 — Cash-Out & Exfiltration
Pre-established LatAm money mule networks disperse funds across multiple accounts within hours of the fraudulent transactions clearing — by the time the organization identifies the anomaly, recovery is largely impossible. Credentials and internal documentation are retained via RAT exfiltration and recycled for future operations against the same organization or connected entities.[1]
Money mule network; C2 infrastructure rotation; Data exfiltration via RAT
Organization bank accounts; Payment processing infrastructure; Internal documentation (retained for future targeting)


